ute magnitudes expected from their spectral types. In both cases,\nit looks as though either the WR components are about 2 magnitudes too bright\nfor their spectral types, or that the O components are about 2 magnitudes too\nfaint. We discuss possible explanations for this apparent discrepancy.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 27 Nov 2001 20:51:24 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-07"}
